FileName: xorg-server-1.20.10.tar.bz2/xorg-server-1.20.10.tar/xorg-server-1.20.10/hw/xfree86/utils/man/cvt.man
SPDXID: SPDXRef-item21009525
FileChecksum: SHA1: 5b471e415261da1f083cd75ad25a78e19509870a
FileChecksum: SHA256: 95f5ee530ea60a8ff10552cc5d20fac75483b11411f6e87f4ed7c308e105c289
FileChecksum: MD5: 69888b4555c464f594b81b6c6ebea26b
LicenseConcluded: LicenseRef-Public-domain
LicenseComments: <text> The information in the file is:
This program is based on the Coordinated Video Timing sample
implementation written by Graham Loveridge. This file is publicly
available at <http://www.vesa.org/Public/CVT/CVTd6r1.xls>. CVT is a
VESA trademark.
We checked the link, it leads to a 404 error. We searched the internet for more information. The only information which we found is at:
https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/xorg/lib/libxcvt/-/blob/master/lib/libxcvt.c?ref_type=heads
These calculations are stolen from the CVT calculation spreadsheet written by Graham Loveridge. He seems to be claiming no copyright and there seems to be no license attached to this. He apparently just wants to see his name mentioned.
 This file can be found at http://www.vesa.org/Public/CVT/CVTd6r1.xls
So we concluded Public-domain as license of this file </text>
LicenseInfoInFile: LicenseRef-Public-domain
FileCopyrightText: NOASSERTION

